opy of a cadet s permanent academic record at the time of issue  All transcripts are issued as a cumulative summary of a cadet s performance at VMI  Transcripts covering a student s secondary and previous college education  which have been submitted to the Institute as a requirement for admission  transfer credit or work completed  and records which are not the property of VMI become a part of the Institute s official file  The Institute will not reissue or certify copies of records from other institutions or certifying officials  Transcripts and records must be ordered directly from the institution of record where the course work was taken  testing conducted or records certified  Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act  FERPA  The Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act  FERPA prohibits the release of personally identifiable information to third party individuals without the expressed written consent of the cadet   student  How To Order A Transcript A transcript will be issued only upon written request by the cadet concerned  Transcript requests must be made in writing  preferably using the VMI Transcript Request Form    This form may be completed and returned via mail or FAX  scanned and emailed or in person to  The Office of the Registrar Virginia Military Institute 303 Shell Hall Lexington  Virginia 24450 FAX  540 464 7726 EMAIL  evanstl vmi edu  NOTE  All requests must be made in writing  including cadet s hand written signature  electronic signatures not accepted  telephone or email requests will not be honored  Information to Include When Requesting a Transcript Full Name While in Attendance Dates of Attendance  Graduation Year or Class Year Name   Address of Recipient  Please be thorough as very often transcripts do not make it to their desired destination due to incomplete address information   include full name  address and zip code  Social Security Number or VMI ID number Name  Address  Phone Number and Email address of where you can be reached  in the event there is a problem processing your request  Original Hand Written Signature of Cadet  Electronic Signatures Not Accepted Processing Fee  payable by cash  check  Visa  MasterCard or Discover  Additional Information Turn Around Time There is a 3 5 work day turnaround for transcripts ordered through the regular process  and 24 work hours for rush requests  NOTE  Processing time includes office processing only  All transcripts are sent via US Mail services  As a result  processing time does NOT include mailing time    Cost  5 00 per copy   3 5 work day turn around   10 00 per copy   24 work hour turn around  includes processing only   not mail time    Transcript Types Official   Official record of performance bearing the Institute seal and provided in a signed and sealed envelope or mailed directly    FAX and Email Services   Fax and Email services are not available for outgoing transcripts  All transcripts are released as official copies in signed sealed envelopes    Overnight Services   Overnight services are not available thru VMI    Restrictions   Virginia Military Institute reserves the right to withhold grades and transcripts for individuals with outstanding administrative or financial obligations with the Institute  Internal Requests No charge   i e  internal scholarship applications  ROTC  etc  Transcript Request Form To download VMI s Transcript Request Form click here  If you have questions please contact VMI s Transcript Coordinator Teresa Evans at 540 464 7213  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY 